cTx6ajkAepIsmh5","label":"participant"},{"source":"recODnfv69EyvRMvA","target":"recSRPfTSaf7TsRiN","label":"participant"},{"source":"recODnfv69EyvRMvA","target":"recgkzNX07a7kGFYL","label":"participant"},{"source":"recODnfv69EyvRMvA","target":"recHrXj4CZl6AH9TQ","label":"location"},{"source":"recODnfv69EyvRMvA","target":"recKrSp5YmwkgRKv0","label":"location"},{"source":"recODnfv69EyvRMvA","target":"rectG8MR4Z2zb8mwZ","label":"predecessor"},{"source":"recODnfv69EyvRMvA","target":"rec4bAiAcAOo9mPwO","label":"part of"}],"verses":[{"id":"recmqxEWGX17FrddA","ref":"Acts.23.23","text":"And he called unto him two centurions, saying, Make ready two hundred soldiers to go to Caesarea, and horsemen threescore and ten, and spearmen two hundred, at the third hour of the night;","year":60},{"id":"recIt59K6ETe81Cdw","ref":"Acts.23.24","text":"And provide them beasts, that they may set Paul on, and bring him safe unto Felix the governor.","year":60},{"id":"recFWfGfco6BUuJLE","ref":"Acts.23.25","text":"And he wrote a letter after this manner:","year":60},{"id":"recYBPjUSU53w1n67","ref":"Acts.23.26","text":"Claudius Lysias unto the most excellent governor Felix sendeth greeting.","year":60},{"id":"recMlSPtrKjhJQPDG","ref":"Acts.23.27","text":"This man was taken of the Jews, and should have been killed of them: then came I with an army, and rescued him, having understood that he was a Roman.","year":60},{"id":"recdebXiWfnMTJrFs","ref":"Acts.23.28","text":"And when I would have known the cause wherefore they accused him, I brought him forth into their council:","year":60},{"id":"recnLRvJcxfopAiPD","ref":"Acts.23.29","text":"Whom I perceived to be accused of questions of their law, but to have nothing laid to his charge worthy of death or of bonds.","year":60},{"id":"recplf6m6yOdYasH4","ref":"Acts.23.30","text":"And when it was told me how that the Jews laid wait for the man, I sent straightway to thee, and gave commandment to his accusers also to say before thee what they had against him. Farewell.","year":60}]}
